SIMPLE: penalty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penalty
<hw>Pe"nal*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Penalties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧nalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Penal</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Penal retribution; punishment for crime or offense; the
suffering in person or property which is annexed by law or judicial
decision to the commission of a crime, offense, or trespass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Death is the <qex>penalty</qex> imposed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The suffering, or the sum to be forfeited, to which
a person subjects himself by covenant or agreement, in case of
nonfulfillment of stipulations; forfeiture; fine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>penalty</qex> and forfeit of my bond.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A handicap.</def> <mark>[Sporting Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>penalty</xex> is in law mostly applied to
a pecuniary punishment.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bill of pains and penalties</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Bill</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>On penalty of</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>Under penalty of</b></col></mcol>, <cd>on pain of;
with exposure to the penalty of, in case of transgression.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penance</ent>⟦br⟧
